arXiv.abstract:
In this paper we discuss Airy solutions of the second Painlev'e equation (\mbox{m P$_{m II}$}) and two related equations, the Painlev'e XXXIV equation ($\mbox{m P}_{34}$) and the Jimbo-Miwa-Okamoto $\sigma$ form of \mbox{m P$_{m II}$}\ (\mbox{m S$_{m II}$}), are discussed. It is shown that solutions which depend only on the Airy function $\mathop{m Ai}
olimits(z)$ have a completely difference structure to those which involve a linear combination of the Airy functions $\mathop{m Ai}
olimits(z)$ and $\mathop{m Bi}
olimits(z)$. For all three equations, the special solutions which depend only on $\mathop{m Ai}
olimits(t)$ are 	extit{tronqu'ee} solutions, i.e.\ they have no poles in a sector of the complex plane. Further for both $\mbox{m P}_{34}$\ and \mbox{m S$_{m II}$}, it is shown that amongst these 	extit{tronqu'ee} solutions there is a family of solutions which have no poles on the real axis.
